  "texts": [
    "(70) has a sharp peak in, then the posterior will have the same sharp peak, and the prior will have little influence.",
    "If, however, the likelihood does not have a single sharp peak, the choice of prior will strongly influence the posterior.",
    "Actually, the situation with is more complicated.",
    "Because of lensing degeneracies, the likelihood can be insensitive to some parameters.",
    "Let us divide the parameters into 'sharp' and 'blunt' = (s, b) such that the likelihood p(D | s, b) is sharply peaked in s and blunt in b."
